sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DSP as Data Science Pipeline API<br/>8888/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant PyPI as PyPI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant KServe as KServe Inference<br/>8080/8443/TCP HTTP/HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Workbench
        User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{user}/lab<br/>HTTPS/443
        Router->>OAuth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS1.2+
        OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth2 Cookie<br/>Check namespace access
        OAuth->>Jupyter: Forward with user headers<br/>HTTP/8888 (localhost)
        Jupyter-->>OAuth: JupyterLab UI HTML
        OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS Response
        Router-->>User: JupyterLab Interface
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,DSP: Flow 2: Submit Data Science Pipeline
        User->>Jupyter: Run notebook cell with Elyra
        Jupyter->>DSP: POST /apis/v1beta1/runs<br/>HTTP/8888 mTLS<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
        DSP->>DSP: Create Argo Workflow
        DSP-->>Jupyter: Pipeline run ID
        Note over DSP: Argo executes pipeline using<br/>Runtime Images (lightweight, no IDE)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,PyPI: Flow 3: Install Python Package at Runtime
        User->>Jupyter: Execute: pip install pandas
        Jupyter->>PyPI: GET /simple/pandas<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
        PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package metadata
        Jupyter->>PyPI: Download package<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
        PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package wheel
        Jupyter->>Jupyter: Install to /opt/app-root/src<br/>(persisted via PVC)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 245)
        Note over Jupyter,S3: Flow 4: Access S3 Data Storage
        User->>Jupyter: Run: boto3.client('s3').get_object()
        Jupyter->>S3: GET /bucket/key<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS Signature v4 (from mounted secret)
        S3-->>Jupyter: Dataset/model artifacts
    end

    rect rgb(245, 240, 255)
        Note over Jupyter,ModelReg: Flow 5: Register Trained Model
        User->>Jupyter: model_registry.register_model()
        Jupyter->>ModelReg: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>HTTP/8080 mTLS<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
        ModelReg-->>Jupyter: Model registration metadata
    end

    rect rgb(255, 255, 230)
        Note over Jupyter,KServe: Flow 6: Deploy Model for Inference
        User->>Jupyter: kubectl apply -f inferenceservice.yaml
        Jupyter->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>via Kubernetes API<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
        KServe-->>Jupyter: Inference endpoint URL
        Jupyter->>KServe: POST /v1/models/mymodel:predict<br/>HTTP/8080 or HTTPS/8443<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
        KServe-->>Jupyter: Prediction results
    end
